        <td width="100%">&nbsp;<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center;text-indent:.5in">
        Applying to Order of the Golden Staff</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in">&nbsp;</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in">OGS does not judge a 
        person on race, level or class therefore all levels, races, and classes 
        are welcome to apply.&nbsp; However OGS does not take in just anybody.&nbsp; We 
        are looking for fun, knowledgeable, loyal, honest, and active adventures 
        who seek a family.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in">To join the ranks of OGS 
        someone in the guild must first refer you.&nbsp; That may mean you have a 
        friend in the guild in RL or in game.&nbsp; Once you have been referred you 
        can fill out our application.&nbsp; You should also check out our <u>
        <a style="color: blue; text-decoration: underline; text-underline: single" href="../charter.asp">
        Charter</a></u> and <u>
        <a style="color: blue; text-decoration: underline; text-underline: single" href="../oath.asp">
        Oath</a></u> to make certain you can abide by these rules. </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in">You will then need three 
        sponsors.&nbsp; Look for OGS members around your level and get to know them 
        through groups, raids, and etc. etc. You should check out our raid rules
        <u>
        <a style="color: blue; text-decoration: underline; text-underline: single" href="raidrules.asp">
        here</a></u>.&nbsp; Please do not simply go around asking members to sponsor 
        you, it does not work that way.&nbsp; OGS members will be looking at your 
        personality, attitude, and they will challenge your skills.&nbsp; Sponsorship 
        is not undertaken lightly.&nbsp; The sponsor is vouching that you are worthy 
        of joining OGS.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in">Once your three sponsors 
        have sent word to the Head of Admissions (Lilyy) or Assistant HoA (Aristana), 
        and you have good standing with all members of the guild, you will be 
        tagged as a pledge.&nbsp; As a pledge you do not receive all the privileges 
        of a full member.&nbsp; Raids will not be conducted specifically for you, you 
        cannot access the member only boards, and you will not be on the guild 
        email list.&nbsp; As a pledge you will be given a mentor.&nbsp; The main purpose 
        of a mentor is to expand a pledges circle of contacts/friends within the 
        guild; and to assign specific tasks with fun and flexibility in mind, 
        that will expand the pledges knowledge/experience.&nbsp; Your mentor is your 
        guide and is usually of the same class or knows about your class.&nbsp; Your 
        mentor will teach you about the OGS mentality and our family.&nbsp; The 
        process can take from two weeks to two months depending on your game 
        time, familiarity of guild members, game knowledge, and your mentor’s 
        schedule as well.&nbsp; If any problems arise while you are a pledge, it will 
        be discussed within the council and with your mentor to hopefully get 
        the problem resolved.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in">Once your mentor deems you 
        ready you will become a full member.&nbsp; A ceremony will be conducted for 
        you and you will then have all the privileges of a full member.&nbsp; </p>
